        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Steward Review Cadence and Exception Handling"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "A stewardship model without a defined review schedule decays quickly. Approvals become stale, risk registers drift from reality, and exceptions go untracked. The review cadence specifies when each type of governance activity must happen, and the exception handling process specifies what to do when something goes wrong between scheduled reviews."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "image",
        "attrs": {
          "src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,",
          "alt": "Steward review calendar and exception trigger flow diagram",
          "title": null
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The diagram shows two complementary views: the annual review calendar (what happens on a predictable schedule) and the exception trigger flow (what happens when an event demands immediate attention). Both feed into the same audit trail."
          }
        ]
      },
