          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Steward review cadence formalises governance into a predictable rhythm: monthly health reports from technical stewards, quarterly asset register refreshes by domain stewards, semi-annual use-case re-approvals with DPO sign-off, and annual policy reviews at the CDO level. Exceptions outside this cadence are classified as P1 (emergency, ≤4h response), P2 (high, ≤5 days), or P3 (standard, ≤10 days), each with defined escalation paths. Log every exception with a structured schema to preserve the audit trail. Enforce review deadlines automatically by adding a governance gate to the CI/CD pipeline that blocks production deployments when any scheduled review is overdue — making compliance a property of the deployment process, not a post-hoc check."
